&lt;h2 id="about"&gt;About
&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Open Measures (fka SMAT) is a project which archives social media data, and
makes that data explorable via APIs or data visualisations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
&lt;img src="https://mixmix.nz/p/open-measures/bar_graphs.png"
width="1600"
height="1155"
srcset="https://mixmix.nz/p/open-measures/bar_graphs_hu_a3244db7b1b0af5e.webp 480w, https://mixmix.nz/p/open-measures/bar_graphs_hu_f63018aab3bba199.webp 1024w"
loading="lazy"
class="gallery-image"
data-flex-grow="138"
data-flex-basis="332px"
&gt;
&lt;img src="https://mixmix.nz/p/open-measures/graph_iteration.jpg"
width="1024"
height="519"
srcset="https://mixmix.nz/p/open-measures/graph_iteration_hu_5dd745ed80d2e1ff.webp 480w, https://mixmix.nz/p/open-measures/graph_iteration_hu_ebed2751359ca033.webp 1024w"
loading="lazy"
class="gallery-image"
data-flex-grow="197"
data-flex-basis="473px"
&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It was designed to support journalists and academics do things like research
the spread of misinformation, identify war criminals, and explore patterns in
discourse.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
&lt;img src="https://mixmix.nz/p/open-measures/war_criminals.png"
